# Sunsynk Home Assistant add-ons

## Editing policy (agents)

**Do not** create, edit, delete, or move files under **`hass-addon-sunsynk-multi/`** unless the user
**explicitly** asks for stable-multi work (e.g. “sync multi”, “release prep”, “fix CI output in
multi”, “cherry-pick to stable addon”). Normal tasks — config, schema, translations, Dockerfile, run
scripts, CHANGELOG in the add-on folder —
**must only be proposed under `hass-addon-sunsynk-edge/`**.

If the user has **`hass-addon-sunsynk-multi/**`** open or asks for a change that would touch multi,
**redirect**: apply the same change under **`hass-addon-sunsynk-edge/`** (or `src/` / docs as below)
and state that multi is updated by **CI when a GitHub tag is pushed**.

## Repository layout

- **`hass-addon-sunsynk-edge`** — **Development add-on.** All manual add-on packaging work happens
  here (`config.yaml`, `schema`, `translations/`, Docker/run scripts).

- **`hass-addon-sunsynk-multi`** — **Stable / release add-on.** **CI-maintained** for routine
  changes; do not hand-edit as part of feature work.

- **`src/ha_addon_sunsynk_multi`** — **Add-on Python** used in the Docker build. Implement behaviour
  here; it ships with edge builds immediately and is what the multi image is built from on release
  (no second code path).

## Supervisor options (documentation workflow)

When you add or change a **Supervisor option**, keep these in sync —
**using edge for packaging strings**:

### 1. Home Assistant UI (`translations/en.yaml`)

- Add or update **`hass-addon-sunsynk-edge/translations/en.yaml`** only (short `name` /
  `description` for the Supervisor UI).
- **Do not** update `hass-addon-sunsynk-multi/translations/` unless the user explicitly requests
  stable-multi sync; CI / release flow is expected to align multi with edge.

### 2. Reference docs (`www/docs/reference/multi-options.md`)

- Document every user-facing option; this page is built into the **VitePress** site. Use the same
  `OPTION_KEY` as in `config.yaml` (uppercase with underscores).

**Dev / edge only:** if the option exists **only** in `hass-addon-sunsynk-edge/config.yaml` (not yet
in multi’s `config.yaml`), prefix the bullet in `multi-options.md` with:

```markdown
- <i-mdi-dev-to class="vp-edge-option-icon" /> `YOUR_OPTION` – …
```

**After release:** when CI adds the option to **`hass-addon-sunsynk-multi/config.yaml`**, remove
that icon prefix and any “edge only” wording for that option (edits to **`multi-options.md`** are
fine; still avoid hand-editing multi **addon** files unless the user asked).

### 3. Python (`src/ha_addon_sunsynk_multi/options.py`)

- Add or update `Options` / `InverterOptions` fields so YAML/env loading matches the edge schema
  (uppercase keys map to lowercase attributes via `mqtt_entity`).
